It probably displayed that it did...didn't bother to take note. <br>
<br>
But no increase in power message means no increase in power pool, and no increase in maximum damage means no use for higher acuity. <br>
<br>
So if you just want to pretend you're cool with some huge charisma stat, go for it! <br>
<br>
Doesn't actually DO anything though.  <br>
<br>
Add +cha gear -&gt; you get the power increase message. <br>
Add acuity to a cloth caster -&gt; maximum damage goes up (no increase in power pool though). <br>
<br>
Lots of people don't understand acuity is only useful for cloth casters, which is why I said something when she listed acuity on her healer but no other abilities that required it. <br>
<br>
The misconception stemmed from the buff increasing piety and intelligence...clerics thought &quot;wow! more piety is good!&quot; but it only increased piety because its the same buff for all three realms and midgard cloth casters use piety as their casting stat. <br>
